  "text": "Pod security context validation in kubernetes/kubernetes is implemented across multiple files and enforced at different levels: API validation and pod security admission policies.\n\n## Core API Validation\nThe primary validation for pod security contexts occurs in `pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go`. This file contains:\n- `ValidateSecurityContext()` (line 7452): Validates SecurityContext fields including privileged mode, runAsUser, runAsGroup, procMount, seccompProfile, allowPrivilegeEscalation, and capabilities\n- `validatePodSpecSecurityContext()` (line 5051): Validates pod-level PodSecurityContext including fsGroup, runAsUser, runAsGroup, supplementalGroups, and seccompProfile\n- `validateSeccompProfileField()` (line 4767): Validates seccomp profile configuration, ensuring valid types (Localhost, RuntimeDefault, Unconfined) and required localhostProfile when type is Localhost\n- `validateSeccompProfileType()` (line 4820): Validates seccomp profile type values\n\n## Pod Security Admission Policy Checks\nPod security policies are enforced through checks in `staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/policy/`, which are applied by the pod security admission webhook:\n\n1. **Privileged Container Validation** (`check_privileged.go`):\n   - `CheckPrivileged()`: Returns a baseline level check (1.0+) forbidding privileged=true\n   - `privileged_1_0()`: Implementation that iterates through containers and checks if SecurityContext.Privileged is set to true\n\n2. **RunAsNonRoot Enforcement** (`check_runAsNonRoot.go`):\n   - `CheckRunAsNonRoot()`: Returns a restricted level check (1.0+) requiring runAsNonRoot=true\n   - `runAsNonRoot_1_0()`: Implementation that validates pod-level and container-level runAsNonRoot settings, with special handling for user namespace pods\n\n3. **Capabilities Validation** (`check_capabilities_restricted.go`):\n   - `CheckCapabilitiesRestricted()`: Returns a restricted level check (1.22+) requiring ALL capabilities to be dropped\n   - `capabilitiesRestricted_1_22()`: Implementation validating that containers drop ALL capabilities and only add NET_BIND_SERVICE\n   - `capabilitiesRestricted_1_25()`: Enhanced version with Windows pod exemption support\n\n4. **Seccomp Profile Enforcement** (`check_seccompProfile_restricted.go`):\n   - `CheckSeccompProfileRestricted()`: Returns a restricted level check (1.19+) requiring RuntimeDefault or Localhost seccomp profiles\n   - `seccompProfileRestricted_1_19()`: Implementation validating seccomp profile types at pod and container levels\n   - `seccompProfileRestricted_1_25()`: Enhanced version with Windows pod exemption support\n\n## Supporting Utilities\n- `visitor.go`: `visitContainers()` function iterates through all containers (init, regular, and ephemeral) for validation\n- `helpers.go`: `relaxPolicyForUserNamespacePod()` provides special handling for user namespace pods\n- `checks.go`: Defines the Check interface and CheckPodFn function type used by all policy checks\n\nThe validation chain starts from `ValidatePodSpec()`, which calls `validatePodSpecSecurityContext()` for pod-level security context validation and `ValidateSecurityContext()` for container-level validation. These functions validate core API requirements. Pod security admission policies then apply additional restrictions based on the pod security level assigned to the namespace."
}

